      "review_text": "Picked this up in Early Access and while it’s still pretty simple right now, the core gameplay is already really fun and you can definitely see the vision.\n\nWhat really hooked me is the daily leaderboard. It gives the same feeling as old arcade games where you kept coming back just to try to get your name on the board. That alone makes it dangerously “one more run” addictive.\n\nThe platforming is straightforward but has a nice challenge to it. Timing your jumps to avoid traps or land on tiny platforms keeps things engaging, so it never really feels like a mindless jumping game. When the instability ramps up it gets harder to stay focused, which adds another layer of difficulty and keeps runs interesting.\n\nOverall it’s already a fun experience and it feels like it’s heading in the right direction. I’m excited to see how it develops during Early Access.",
      "timestamp_created": 1773785497
    },
    {
      "review_id": "221023290",
      "author_steamid": "76561198216152993",
      "voted_up": true,
      "votes_up": 2,
      "playtime_at_review": 28,
      "review_text": "This is my first time ever writing a review, but I wanted to say I really like this game. I’ve never really played games like this before, but in a weird way it kind of reminded me of the classic Mario games, just way more sci-fi, intense, and heart-pumping because you never really know what’s going to happen next. That’s what made it fun for me. I also really like the daily run because I like seeing what everybody’s doing on the leaderboard and how far they get. It pumps me up because if somebody gets far, it makes me want to try and get even farther than them. I can see where this game is headed, and I think it’s really good. I’ve been enjoying it a lot. 10/10👍👍",
      "timestamp_created": 1773889103
    }
  ]
}